<br>
Something must have hurt your feelings, or maybe having to read so much is more than you can muster.  Personally, I don't have a problem reading or writing (or spelling, for that matter).<br>
<br>
Why does it bother you that I make these rational arguments that make your head spin?<br>
<br>
If you think it is all &quot;spin&quot;, as you say, then explain to me in words how what I say is wrong.  Specifically, if crack is so much worse than alcohol, why?  Crack can kill its user immediately if he smokes too much (heart attack).  Alcohol can kill its user if he drinks too much (heart stops).  I remember Secretary's Day in 1983.  A Carmel, Indiana nightclub held a Peppermint Schnapps drinking contest for ladies.  21 women were hospitalized and 9 died.  Perfectly healthy women.  Perfectly legal contest.  Dead of a drug overdose.<br>
<br>
