<br>
I think you might be less uncomfortable if you opened your mind a little.  When you try to cram reason into a small and enclosed space, it can really hurt. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bfcavconservatives.showUserPublicProfile?gid=therightguyatfcav>The Right Guy at FCAV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(1/11/04 7:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffcavconservativesfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Milkchaser....Re: Tsk, Tsk</span><hr size=1> If you truly are a Republican, you are in a miniscule minority!<br>
<br>
The drug war is working! Why quit now?<br>
<br>
Just last week it was reported on FOX news that only 10% of all drugs headed for distribution in the USA actually hits the streets. That means, in one way or another, the drug war is making a huge difference. And personally, I would pay a little more tax to keep more law breakers in jail, but I have 2 requirements that must first be met by our Government before I would vote yes for a raise in my taxes for this purpose.<br>
<br>
1. Cut back dramatically on Govnt waste!<br>
<br>
2. Start deporting illegal alliens. A good place to start would be our prisons. Instead of the American taxpayer keeping up illegals because they broke our laws, ship them back! <br>
<br>
David<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bfcavconservatives.showUserPublicProfile?gid=milkchaser>milkchaser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(1/11/04 9:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffcavconservativesfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Milkchaser....Re: Tsk, Tsk</span><hr size=1> Some polls show that 80% of the American public supports legalized marijuana for medical patients -- I'm not so sure who's in the minority, you or me.<br>
<br>
Today I got stuck in traffic.  It took about an hour to go 4 miles along a two-lane interstate.  Some people in the other lane saw my &quot;Stop the War&quot; bumper sticker and asked me what I meant.  I told them I wanted to see drugs legalized.  All three of them smiled from ear to ear.  &quot;We just wanted to see what side you were on&quot;, said one woman.<br>
<br>
So I'm not so sure which of us is in the minority.<br>
<br>
I don't think one person should tell another what to do with his life.  To try to dictate another person's lifestyle when it has no obvious effect on you is nothing more than a form of indirect slavery.  As Lincoln said (a Republican, mind you), as I would not be a slave, so I would not be a master.<br>
<br>
But then some continue to try to control others, I suspect because they are not sure they can keep their own life in order (but that's just a suspicion).<br>
<br>
As for illegal immigration, there's an issue we can agree on.  I don't know if you are aware of this, but the BCIS (formerly known as the INS) has 4.5 million pending immigration cases.  They are tremendously backlogged.  In other words, there's no way they can handle their current caseload.<br>
<br>
So now Bush wants to lay 7 to 10 million more cases on them?  How are they going to handle that?  Well, one way is to just wave everybody in.  But then, if they do that, how will they know which ones really have a job, which ones are dangerous (possibly former criminals).  <br>
<br>
If a man marries a foreign woman, after two years she can apply for legal permanent residence.  It used to take 3 months to wait for a 15 minute interview, during which they check to make sure that the marriage is real and not just for immigration purposes.  Now it is taking 2 years to schedule that 15 minute interview.  That's how backlogged they are.<br>
<br>
So how are they going to do any genuine checking if, with the stroke of a pen, their caseload is doubled?!!<br>
<br>
In short, despite what they say that the Bush administration is only bowing to reality by facing the throng of illegals we already have, they are, in fact, in la-la land, with no real plan to solve the problem.  The only thing that will get solved by this is that a whole lot of legal, voting Hispanic-Americans will be tempted to vote for Bush.<br>
<br>
Which, as a Republican I have to say is the only silver lining to a very bad policy decision.  It really makes me wonder if we elected the right Republican in 2000.  OTOH, if he gets social security reform (ie. private accounts) and yet more tax cuts, I suppose we have to take the bad with the good.<br>
<br>
But back to the drug issue... If, as so many conservatives are now saying, we have to face reality and deal with 7 to 10 million illegal aliens, then why do we not also have to face the 10 million+ Americans -- tax-paying, otherwise law-abiding citizens, mind you -- who smoke marijuana at least once a month?  <br>
<br>
There are times when we as a society have to recognize that we do not live in a perfect world.  Just as it would be impossibly impractical to arrest and deport 7 to 10 million aliens, it is also ridiculous to suggest that we could arrest and house in prisons 10 million marijuana users.  Currently, there are only 2 million prisoners in the federal prison system (perhaps as many more in state prisons).  <br>
<br>
We have to face that we could not every really arrest and imprison twice as many prisoners in jails that are already overcrowded.  And that's not to mention the dramatic negative effect it would have on families and businesses nationwide.  If you think that deporting all the illegal aliens would have an effect on low-level employment (hotel maids, restaurant workers, gardners, pool boys, etc), imagine what would happen when we start locking up doctors, lawyers, teachers, engineers, scientists, hairdressers, hotel managers, store owners, car mechanics, carpenters, plumbers, dry cleaners, etc, etc.  The decline in productivity and hike in the cost of local, state and federal gov't would throw this country into Depression!  Think about it -- a 2% decline in GDP is considered a harsh recession.  What would happen to the economy when you subtract 10% of its workforce across the socio-economic spectrum?  <br>
<br>
So, realistically speaking, we cannot and should not actually enforce our drug laws.  It's like speed limits -- most people break that law most of the time.  We don't actually expect the law to be enforced, we complain bitterly when we actually get caught.<br>
<br>
If you're like me, this seems a little crazy.<br>
<br>
And, despite what you suggested, the drug war is not succeeding by any means.  For 30 years we have been saying that we want to eliminate drug use and for 30+ years we have made no dent in the demand.<br>
<br>
As for interdicting 90% of the supply, as you heard on Fox, this is ludicrous, when you think about it.  The gov't has no idea how, when and where drugs cross the border (or, in the case of methamphetamines and pot -- where it is made or grown).  If they knew, they'd arrest the distributors, no?  And yet, people somehow keep getting a supply through means and routes the gov't has no knowledge of.<br>
<br>
By definition, if the drugs are getting through, even if it takes 9 shipments to get 1 shipment in, the drug war has failed.  And in fact, the price and supply of drugs is about where it used to be (in fact, cocaine is somewhat cheaper, I'm told, that it was back in the 80's when I used it).<br>
<br>
But in another way, the drug war is more than an ineffective and expensive gov't boondoggle.  Plenty of gov't programs fit that description, but few of them end up killing innocent people.  If you care about others (as Christians are supposedly wont to do), you would learn about the various people who are killed by police during drug raids.  Many have absolutely nothing to do with drugs.  Oops.  Sorry.  Promise not to do it again.<br>
<br>
Then there's the corruption problem.  Given the enormous sums of money the drug distributors are bringing in, the temptation for corruption is just too much even for our good American police.  Frankly, I don't blame them, because THESE ARE STUPID LAWS in the first place. But then, you knew I felt this way.<br>
<br>
You know, we don't agree on this issue and I feel very strongly that I have made a Conservative argument.  I wish that you would search your heart and find a way to at least stop questioning my conservative credentials.  Just because we disagree, that doesn't mean I am not a Conservative.  Who knows?  You may even someday see that I have a point and change your mind on the issue.  That sometimes happens when a person keeps an open mind and tries to reason through issues rather than cling stubbornly inside his comfort zone. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bfcavconservatives.showUserPublicProfile?gid=milkchaser>milkchaser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(1/12/04 2:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffcavconservativesfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Milkchaser....Re: Tsk, Tsk</span><hr size=1> In my last message, I did not mean to endorse breaking the law.  I said that I could understand why a cop would be corrupted by drug money, but the fact is, I like to think that I could never be corrupted if I were in their place.<br>
<br>
In fact, one of the reasons I am a Republican is that I believe it is important to obey the law, and I was revolted by the sight of Democrat Bill Clinton flouting the law.<br>
<br>
So I never should have been so flippant about such a serious matter as police corruption.  I apologize for that stupid remark.  <br>
<br>
And I also do not endorse meth making or pot growing either.  These are dangerous and stupid things to do.  I would be really angry if this kind of thing went on in my neighborhood and I take it for granted that it doesn't.<br>
<br>
I only meant to bring to light the easiness of these forms of drug production -- not that I approve of them.  In fact, one of the biggest disadvantages of our current law is that these drugs are not distributed through safe and legal means.  Even though some of these drugs are unsafe (like alcohol and cigarettes) that doesn't mean that people should have to make their own (can you imagine making your own whisky or growing your own tobacco?), nor should these users have to conspire with criminals (as people had to do with bootleggers in the 1920s &amp; 30s).<br>
<br>
But until this country, as I put it in the previous post, faces that it can't plausibly enforce its unrealistic drug laws and changes them, I don't even endorse using, buying or possessing these substances.  And even if they were legal, I would warn against using almost all of them for health reasons, both psychological and physical.<br>
<br>
I don't smoke cigarettes.  My dad died from emphysema.  If you've ever seen the effects of that disease, you know that it's not very encouraging when someone you love suffers from it.  But I would never want to see tobacco outlawed.  I know that this country would be worse off for it.  My dad did a very foolish thing, and he repeated it literally thousands of times:  he lit every cigarette he smoked, near about.  He killed himself slowly.  But he was free to do so, and that is as it should be.  <br>
<br>
So I am the last person to endorse using, making or distributing tobacco, but I do support legal tobacco.  I hope that makes my position clear. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bfcavconservatives.showUserPublicProfile?gid=therightguyatfcav>The Right Guy at FCAV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(1/12/04 8:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffcavconservativesfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Milkchaser....Re: Tsk, Tsk</span><hr size=1> It's very hard for me to understand why you argue so strongly about this particular issue. Unless you use the drugs yourself.<br>
<br>
In one of your posts you suggested that there should be no difference between alcohol and drugs. We actually agree on this one. Why don't you put as much effort into outlawing alcohol. Even though I drink an occasional beer, I would have no problem with giving it up. Tobacco too!<br>
<br>
Yes, I understand that the chance of alcohol being outlawed are slim-to-none. These are the same odds I give to legalizing drugs.<br>
<br>
David <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffcavconservativesfrm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=14.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffcavconservativesfrm2.showNextMessage?topicID=14.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffcavconservativesfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=13><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/black_default/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffcavconservativesfrm2.emailToFriend?topicID=14.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffcavconservativesfrm2.threadControl?topicID=14.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/black_default/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffcavconservativesfrm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=14.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/ffcavconservativesfrm2.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=14.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub98.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1